# ==========================================================================
# Image WEB (deploy/Dockerfile) — Django service + the 8 Cloud Run jobs.
# ==========================================================================
# Versions are NOT pinned here: they are inherited from the union lockfile via
# the constraint below. Edit versions in requirements.in, recompile it, then
# recompile this file:
#   pip-compile --allow-unsafe --strip-extras --output-file=requirements-web.txt requirements-web.in
#
# Torch note: this image is CPU-only. The Dockerfile pre-installs torch from
# the PyTorch CPU index (same trick as CI) BEFORE installing this lock, so the
# `torch` pin below is satisfied by the +cpu wheel and the multi-GB nvidia-*
# CUDA wheels are never pulled.
#
# Kept ML stack rationale: the 8 Cloud Run jobs run manage.py tasks that
# import torch/transformers/sentence-transformers/peft/trl IN-PROCESS
# (train_vibe_*, continuous_pretraining, train_expert_model, distillation,
# evaluation_metrics) and rlhf_pipeline shells out to the dbt CLI — so the
# training/dbt stack must stay, only CUDA and the GPU-only serving libs
# (diffusers, coqui-tts) move to the brain image.
-c requirements.txt

# 1. Web Application & API Frameworks
Django
djangorestframework
drf-spectacular
channels
channels-redis
daphne
django-cors-headers
django-environ
django-filter
django-prometheus
django-ratelimit
django-csp
django-storages
gunicorn
uvicorn
whitenoise

# 2. Databases, Vector Stores, Caches & ORM Clients
django-redis
neo4j
psycopg2-binary
redis

# 3. ML/AI (CPU: embeddings, rerank fallback, in-process job training)
bitsandbytes
google-genai
numba
numpy
peft
sentence-transformers
torch
transformers
trl
imageio
z3-solver
accelerate

